#+TITLE: Some stirring quotes


“Excellence can be obtained if you CARE more than others think is wise,
RISK more than others think is safe, DREAM more than others think is practical,
and EXPECT more than others think is possible.” -- Author Unknown (attr? Claude Bissell, Michaelangelo, ...)

There are two ways to slide easily through life; to believe everything
or to doubt everything. Both ways save us from thinking.  -- Alfred Korzybski

By relieving the brain of all unnecessary work, a good notation sets it
free to concentrate on more advanced problems. -- Alfred North Whitehead

A Key to Wisdom:  Strong opinions that are weakly held.

Attributed to Paul Saffo of the Palo Alto Institue of the Future.

"[He] explained that weak opinions are problematic because people aren't
inspired to develop the best arguments possible for them, or to put forth the
energy required to test them. [He] explained that it was just as important,
however, to not be too attached to what you believe because, otherwise, it
undermines your ability to see and hear evidence that clashes with your
opinions."  -- Bob Sutton (http://bobsutton.typepad.com/my_weblog/2006/07/strong_opinions.html)


